clean term cache "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
================================================================

NAME
----

clean term cache - Will remove all of the term ids from the cache.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Will remove all of the term ids from the cache.

USAGE
-----

` <?php clean_term_cache( $ids, $taxonomy, $clean_taxonomy ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$ids` 
:   ([*int|array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int.7Carray "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Single or list of Term IDs
    Default: *None*

 `$taxonomy` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Can be empty and will assume tt\_ids, else will use for
    context.
    Default:

 `$clean_taxonomy` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to clean taxonomy wide caches (true), or just
    individual term object caches (false). Default is true.
    Default: true

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.3](/Version_2.3 "Version 2.3")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`clean_term_cache()` is located in `wp-includes/taxonomy.php`

